---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "March 29, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for Draigon Idle — the rules governing your use of the game and website."
>
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="terms-title">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="section-title" id="terms-title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="section-body">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <p>
          Please read these Terms of Service ("<strong>Terms</strong>")
          carefully before using the Draigon Idle mobile game
          (the "<strong>Game</strong>") or the website draigonidle.com
          (the "<strong>Site</strong>"), both operated by Stonemill Studios
          ("<strong>we</strong>," "<strong>us</strong>," or
          "<strong>our</strong>").
        </p>
        <p>
          By downloading, installing, or playing the Game, or by accessing
          the Site, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not
          agree, do not use the Game or Site.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be at least 13 years old to use the Game or Site. By
          using the Game or Site, you represent that you meet this
          requirement. If you are under the age of majority in your
          jurisdiction, you represent that a parent or guardian has reviewed
          and agreed to these Terms on your behalf.
        </p>

        <h2>2. License to Play</h2>
        <p>
          Subject to these Terms, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive,
          non-transferable, revocable license to download and play the Game
          for your personal, non-commercial use. This license does not include
          the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Modify, reverse-engineer, or decompile the Game</li>
          <li>Redistribute or resell access to the Game</li>
          <li>Use the Game for commercial purposes without our written consent</li>
          <li>Exploit bugs or glitches for unfair advantage</li>
          <li>Use third-party tools to automate gameplay</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Virtual Items and Currency</h2>
        <p>
          The Game may include virtual currencies, items, or other
          digital content (collectively, "<strong>Virtual Items</strong>").
          Virtual Items have no real-world monetary value, cannot be
          transferred or redeemed for real money, and are licensed to you
          — not sold. We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or remove
          Virtual Items at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>4. User Conduct</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Harass, threaten, or harm other players</li>
          <li>Engage in cheating, hacking, or exploiting the Game</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems</li>
          <li>Impersonate Stonemill Studios or any of our staff</li>
          <li>Use the Game or Site for any unlawful purpose</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content in the Game and on the Site — including art, music,
          text, code, characters, world design, and the Draigon Idle name
          and logo — is the exclusive property of Stonemill Studios and is
          protected by copyright, trademark, and other applicable laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works from
          our content without our prior written permission, except for
          personal fan art and non-commercial community content shared with
          clear attribution.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Cloud Saves and Game Data</h2>
        <p>
          If you use the cloud save feature, your game data is stored on our
          servers via Firebase Firestore. While we take reasonable precautions
          to protect your data, we cannot guarantee against all loss or
          corruption. You are responsible for maintaining any local backups
          you consider important.
        </p>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to reset, modify, or delete cloud save data as
          required for maintenance, security, or to address violations of
          these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          The Game and Site are provided "<strong>as is</strong>" without
          warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that
          the Game will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful
          components. Your use of the Game is at your own risk.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, Stonemill Studios
          shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of, or
          inability to use, the Game or Site — including loss of data or
          game progress.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We may suspend or terminate your access to the Game at our
          discretion, with or without notice, if you violate these Terms or
          engage in conduct we deem harmful to the Game or its community.
          Upon termination, your license to use the Game immediately ends.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. When we do, we will
          revise the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued
          use of the Game or Site after changes are posted constitutes your
          acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which
          Stonemill Studios is incorporated, without regard to conflict of
          law principles.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Contact us at:
        </p>
        <address>
          Stonemill Studios<br />
          <a href="mailto:legal@stonemillstudios.com">legal@stonemillstudios.com</a>
        </address>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-content {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    max-width: 72ch;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .legal-content > * + * {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .legal-content ul li + li {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .legal-content address {
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .legal-content strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
  }
</style>
